# GitHub Basics

## 📌 Introduction
This repository is created to understand the basics of GitHub, version control, and collaborative project management. It is mainly designed for academic learning and beginner-level practice.

## 🎯 Objective
- Learn how to create and manage repositories  
- Understand version control concepts  
- Practice uploading and managing files  
- Gain confidence in using GitHub for projects  

## ⚙️ Tools Used
- GitHub  
- Web Browser  
- Basic text editor  

## 📂 Features
- Creating repositories  
- Adding and managing files  
- Using README for documentation  
- Understanding commits and updates  

## 🚀 How to Use
1. Create a repository  
2. Add files using “Add File” option  
3. Write content in README  
4. Commit changes  
5. Share repository link  

## 🤝 Collaboration
GitHub allows multiple users to work together by sharing repositories and contributing to projects.

## 📘 Learning Outcome
- Improved understanding of GitHub  
- Knowledge of version control system  
- Ability to manage academic projects online  

